quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  11,20,"By no means will they escape on earth, nor have they protectors besides Allah! Their torment will be doubled! They could not bear to listen and they used not to see (the truth)"
  11,21,"They are those who have lost their own selves, and that which they invented eluded them"
  11,22,"Certainly, they are those who will be the greatest losers in the Hereafter"
  11,23,"Verily, those who believe and do righteous good deeds, and humble themselves before their Lord, they will be the dwellers of Paradise to dwell therein forever"
  11,24,The likeness of the two parties is as the blind and the deaf and the seer and the hearer. Are they equal when compared Will you not then take heed
  11,25,"And indeed We sent Nuh to his people (and he said): \"I have come to you as a plain warner"
  11,26,"That you worship none but Allah; surely, I fear for you the torment of a painful Day"
  11,27,"The chiefs who disbelieved among his people said: \"We see you but a man like ourselves, nor do we see any follow you but the meanest among us and they (too) followed you without thinking. And we do not see in you any merit above us, in fact we think you are liars"
  11,28,"He said: \"O my people! Tell me, if I have a clear proof from my Lord, and a mercy (prophethood) has come to me from Him, but that (mercy) has been obscured from your sight. Shall we compel you (to accept) it when you have a strong hatred for it"